https://api.eclipse.org/

Eclipse Api RESTful API

Eclipse Fountation resources and data.

Authentication ¶

Eclipse Api RESTful API uses OAuth Authorization for protected resources.

Error States ¶

The common HTTP Response Status Codes are used.

MarketPlace Favorites ¶

The Eclipse MarketPlace is a place to discover, share, and install relevant Eclipse plugins and solutions. Think of it like an app store for Eclipse solutions.

Resource Group ¶

Favorites  ¶

List of all the Eclipse MarketPlace Favorites.

Retrieve Favorites
GET/marketplace/favorites{content_id}{?name,page,pagesize}

Example URI

GET https://api.eclipse.org//marketplace/favoritescontent_id?name=&page=&pagesize=
URI Parameters
HideShow
content_id
string (optional) 

Unique identifier of the listing, i.e, 123, 134.

name
string (optional) 

A valid Eclipse username.

page
integer (optional) 

The index of the page to get, defaults to 1.

pagesize
integer (optional) 

The number of records to get per page, defaults to 20. Maximum value is 100.
